goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the frequency of flight distances and the range of distances covered by flights.

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=origin_counts.index, y=origin_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Origin Airport')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.title('What is the most common origin airport?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    avg_delay_by_origin = data.groupby('origin')['delay'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='origin', y='delay', data=avg_delay_by_origin)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average delay time for each origin airport?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
